Marcus Tang was a Political Science and Communication student at UC Davis (20062010). During his time on campus he served as ASUCD ASUCDs Academic Affairs Commission Chair, a peer advisor in the College of Letters & Science, a board member for the Campus Rotaract Club of Davis, the Centennial Director for the Student Alumni Association, a member of the Aggie Recruitment Team, and a Davis Honors Challenge student. He loves UC Davis so much that he bleeds Aggies Aggie blue and gold. During the 20082009 academic year he was seriously consideredand ultimately was a finalistby the Picnic Day Board of Directors for the honor of the 2009 Picnic Day Student Parade Marshal.
